BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Natural Heritage of Indiana 1\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260402T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260402T150000
UID:8d120e187b6f24a2aaa1cc4748964179@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a film by documentary filmmaker Samuel Orr. The Na
 tural Heritage of Indiana is based on Marion Jackson&#39\;s book of the sa
 me title. Take an in depth look at Indiana&#39\;s natural beauty\, with in
 teresting information and fantastic cinemotography. The film will last abo
 ut an hour. Today is Part I: The Indiana That Was.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\, Nashvi
 lle\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Strahl Lake Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260402T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260402T154500
UID:69449ff4b639c3887bcf5a3a9a33270e@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided hike of Trail 6 around Lak
 e Strahl! Hear about the history of the lake\, the surrounding Strahl Vall
 ey\, and learn about the animals that make it their home. The section of T
 rail 6 around Lake Strahl is considered easy to moderate. It has some shor
 t staircases\, uneven surfaces\, and wet spots. The trail is less than a m
 ile and will take about 45 minutes to complete.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Lake Strahl parking lot\, 1405 S.R. 46 
 W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
