BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Campfire Storytime\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260403T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260403T194500
UID:6ebd97498dcc877c0e39ae1d2bff6ea9@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join the nature center mascots\, Olive the Owl and Doug the De
 er\, and a park naturalist for a story reading. We will read Owl Moon and 
 enjoy a small campfire at the edge of the woods. Meet at the fire ring beh
 ind the Friends&#39\; Shelterhouse near the Nature Center. Come early to e
 njoy the fire if you like! We will take suggestions on kid friendly books 
 about nature! Feel free to suggest a favorite of yours to the naturalist! 
 Owl Moon\, The Lorax\, and Zee Grows A Tree are popular titles\, but we&#3
 9\;d love to add more variety!
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center (Friends' Circle)\, 1405 
 S.R. 46 W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260403T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260403T220000
UID:230c32b68696f591314ccd2a9a99b4f3@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided night hike around Lake Ogl
 e! The Full Moon is the brightest night of the month\, leading to excellen
 t views of the lake. Learn about April&#39\;s full moon\, the Pink Moon. T
 rail 7 is rated moderate\, but should be considered rugged in the dark. Th
 e trail has some staircases\, uneven surfaces\, and muddy spots. It is 1.2
  miles and will take about an hour and a half to complete. Please do not b
 ring pets on night hikes. Red flashlights are preferred for night vision a
 nd can be loaned to hikers on request.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Lake Ogle parking lot\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\
 , Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
