BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Morel Mushroom Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260405T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260405T103000
UID:6330af990c90b8d814fa536fda4f6e72@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a short guided hike at Strahl Lake.
  Learn how to spot morels\, the rules for hunting and keeping them in the 
 park\, and what you might use them for. Keep your eyes on the ground as we
  look for wildflowers and mushrooms to identify. The section of Trail 6 ar
 ound the lake is half a mile\, with some more off trail hiking. There are 
 some slopes and uneven surfaces. Close toed shoes are recommended.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Strahl Lake\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\, Nashvill
 e\, IN 
URL:on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
